#Approach:

Approach (Hinglish):

DLL sorted hai, isliye two-pointer approach use kar sakte hain.

Step 1:
Left pointer ko head pe rakho.

Step 2:
Right pointer ko last node tak le jao.

Step 3:
Ab left aur right ka sum nikaalo:
- agar sum target se chhota hai, left ko aage badhao
- agar sum target se bada hai, right ko peeche lao
- agar sum target ke equal hai, pair store karo
  aur dono pointers move karo

Step 4:
Loop tab tak chalega jab tak left aur right cross na kar jayein.

Kyuki list sorted hai, isliye har step pe decide kar sakte hain
ki left badhana hai ya right ghataana hai.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1) extra space
(output list ko छोड़कर)

#Code:

/*
class ListNode {
    int val;
    ListNode next;
    ListNode prev;
    
    ListNode(int val) {
        this.val = val;
        this.next = null;
        this.prev = null;
    }
}
*/

class Solution {
    public List<List<Integer>> findPairsWithGivenSum(ListNode head, int target) {
        // Your code goes here
        List<List<Integer>> ans = new ArrayList<>();
        if(head == null){
            return ans;
        }
        ListNode left = head;
        ListNode right = head;

        while(right.next != null){
            right = right.next;
        }

        while(left.val < right.val){
            int sum = left.val + right.val;
            if(sum < target){
                left = left.next;
            }
            else if(sum > target){
                right = right.prev;
            }
            else{
                List<Integer> temp = new ArrayList<>();
                temp.add(left.val);
                temp.add(right.val);
                ans.add(temp);
                left = left.next;
                right = right.prev;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
